    <p>Solar panel costs in Rhode Island typically range from \$2.90 to \$3.20 per watt installed before incentives. For a typical 8kW residential system, homeowners can expect to pay between \$23,200 and \$25,600 before applying the 30% federal tax credit and state incentives. After the federal tax credit, the net cost drops to approximately \$16,240 to \$17,920. When factoring in Rhode Island's REG program payments and National Grid rebates, many homeowners see payback periods of 7-10 years, after which they enjoy essentially free electricity for the remainder of the system's 25+ year warranty period.</p>
  </div>
